<div class="recipes">
<div class="mainTitle">Spicy dry beef</div>
<div class="ingredientList">
 <li>Prep time: 15 Minutes</li>
 <li>Cook time: 1-2 Hours</li>
 <li>Serves: 4</li>
</div>
<div class="secondaryTitles">Ingredients</div>
<div class="ingredientList">
 <li>1kg Sliced beef</li>
 <li>1 tbsp chilli sauce</li>
 <li>3 tbsp tamari</li>
 <li>1 tbsp sugar (optional)</li>
 <li>3-4 pieces licorice root</li>
 <li>1 thumb sized piece ginger</li>
 <li>2 star anise</li>
 <li>1/4 tsp cloves</li>
<div class="line"></div>
</div>
                
<div class="ingredientList"></div>
 <div class="secondaryTitles">Step 1</div>
 <p>Saute sliced beef then cover with water
 </p>
 <div class="secondaryTitles">Step 2</div>
 <p>Add spices then simmer until reduced
 </p>
 <div class="secondaryTitles">Step 3</div>
 <p>If you want, add sliced onion 15 minutes before serving
 </p>
 <div class="secondaryTitles">Step 4</div>
 <p>Cook until tender & almost dry
 </p>
</div>
